(2773, 'the-flying-house', 1, 52, 24, 'The series began in the middle of a game of hide and seek, as a young boy named Justin Casey (Gen) finishes counting and begins searching for his friends Angela (usually called \"Angie\") and Corkey Roberts (Kanna and Tsukubo Natsuyama).rnrnAs he searched for the brother and sister in the wooded area, a storm occurred all of a sudden. Justin managed to sneak up on the two before the rain started pouring, forcing them to run for cover. They would eventually find a house in the wooded area, previously unseen according to Justin. At first glance it appeared nobody was home after entering the house, until they discovered a robot named Solar Ion Robot (Kadenchin), or the acronym SIR. They would soon meet the owner of the house, Professor Humphrey Bumble (Dr. Tokio Taimu), who introduced the children to his greatest creation, a time machine. Professor Bumble\'s attempt at recreating Benjamin Franklin\'s famous lightning experiment with the use of a kite flying outside the house to get the machine working only led up to SIR\'s temporary change in personality before sending the entire house on course for the past.rnrnThe children never realized how long the journey back home would be due to Professor Bumble\'s misguidance and errors in time travel, but in the meantime they witnessed and participated (with little or no consequences) in numerous events in the Bible\'s New Testament, from John the Baptist\'s birth to the rise of the Apostle Paul.rnrn(Source: Wikipedia)', '', '2013-02-20 19:43:13', '2015-08-30 03:44:28', 'N', 'N', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 41, 'All Ages', 1, '1982-04-05', '1983-03-28', 0, 'A3650-84.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 0, 2015, 0, 0, 0, 'en', 'N', 30654),
(2778, 'anime-tenchou', 1, 1, 2, 'This is the Animation Store Manager!!rnAnime Tenchou is a CM character for Animate, one of Japan\'s biggest retailer of anime, games, and manga. The character series was created by Shimamoto Kazuhiko for publicity purposes. Later adapted into a manga, a weekly radio drama and this OVA animated by GAINAX and directed by Anno Hideaki.rnAnizawa Meito is the blazing store manager. He is a fireball who loves animation merchandise at heart. He takes over the dying wish of the former store manager, though still alive, who was attacked by the rival store and becomes a “store manager” of newly opened animation goods specialty store, Animate. The scarlet, “store manager visor” is his trademark.rn(Source: AniDB)', 'N', '2013-02-20 19:43:17', '2016-07-04 03:03:35', 'N', 'N', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 3.0305989066196433, 659, 'All Ages', 3, '2002-08-19', '0000-00-00', 0, '2778.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 0, 2014, 0, 0, 0, 'en_jp', 'N', 43388),
(2781, 'koharu-biyori', 3, 3, 30, 'Set in a near future, a time where robots are common workers for their owners. Takaya Murase has just purchased a maid robot from a robotic doll distriubutor, MaidWorks. Ready to live a normal cleaning, cooking, and serving life to her owner, Yui is purchased, by Takaya but he has other plans for her...like dressing her up in dress-costumes of his fantasies and more.rn(Source: ANN)', '', '2013-02-20 19:43:19', '2016-07-04 03:03:35', 'N', 'N', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 3.2182011159411674, 850, 'Mild Nudity', 3, '2007-10-14', '2008-03-21', 0, '2781.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 0, 2014, 0, 0, 0, 'en_jp', 'N', 48259),
(2782, 'strait-jacket', 3, 3, 26, 'It is a world where magic and science coexist. Rayotte Steinberg, a lone wolf “tactical sorcerist”, fights against monsters. They used to be human beings, but they had overused the forbidden power, “magic”, and turned into monsters. He wears a “mold”, the straitjacket that keeps him human. In his hand he wields a “staff”, a magical wand that detonates everything in his path. Everytime he uses \"magic\", he moves one step closer to becoming a monster, but if he doesn’t, he will be killed. During the harsh battles, he will face a sin he had committed in the past.nn(Source: AnimeNfo)', '', '2013-02-20 19:43:20', '2016-07-04 03:03:35', '318321.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 115238, '2014-11-18 03:01:14', 3.3707908140674365, 1291, 'Violence, Profanity', 3, '2007-11-26', '2008-04-28', 0, 'strait-jacket.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 0, 2015, 80, 0, 0, 'en_jp', 'N', 66231),
